This is a great time to dynamite Black's proud pawn centre with [[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...e5/2. Nf3/2...Nc6/3. Bb5/3...f5/4. Nc3/4...fxe4/5. Nxe4/5...d5/6. Nxe5|'''6. Nxe5''']]! White comes out of the resulting tactics in good shape.

[[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...e5/2. Nf3/2...Nc6/3. Bb5/3...f5/4. Nc3/4...fxe4/5. Nxe4/5...d5/6. Ng3|'''6. Ng3''']] isn't exactly a bad move, and Black still has to do something about the threat to the e-pawn, but who wants to let Black play ...e5 and ...d5 in the first 5 moves and get away with it?{{wikipedia|Ruy_Lopez#Schliemann_Defence:_3...f5}}{{Chess Opening Theory/Footer}}
